99800000,"eeoi":3.287169258920402000,"aer":4.542729110216294000,"soxMt":4.714200000000000000,"sox":0.009584629460201280,"noxMt":51.750000000000000000,"nox":0.105215004574565410,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Rio de Janeiro","displayOrder":0,"co2":0.000000000000000000,"eeoi":0.000000000000000000,"aer":0.000000000000000000,"soxMt":0.000000000000000000,"sox":0.000000000000000000,"noxMt":0.000000000000000000,"nox":0.000000000000000000,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2022-10-14T04:09:07.767","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Correcting hire days and ballast/laden bunkers"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-10-12T13:25:57.113","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Good day,\nPlease find below intermediate calculation for Stena Provence (diesel, gasoline)\nIntermediate Link\n\u2022\tPre-calc:               $10,572 x 68.2 days = ($336,113)\n\n\u2022\tEarnings:              $11,233 x 69.05 days = ($294,665)\nDifference:    Below fixture note best describes the structure on this TC/CVC with J-Global.  Essentially we are paid hire and an admin (think commercial management) fee while rebilling all voyage expenses.  Sounds simple enough, but a lot of manipulating in VMS was needed to properly track and allocate the expenses appropriately.  It\u2019s a great exercise\u2026aka operational challenge\u2026to ensure figures within VMS lined up with the various expense/invoice breakdown requests from J-Global, but good teamwork across the desk made it possible.  With an additional 1.9 days of hire at $25k/pd, we were able boost the earnings slightly as compared to initial estimate.  The next voyage should be less challenging from an administrative side as all time will count.\nImprovements:  No improvements worth noting, but wanted to give Carol a big shout for all her help on this one!\n\nFixture Notes:\n\nFirst Voyage of the new hybrid TC / CVC with J global which is equivalent to min 18,000 max 25,000 pd on r/t bss. Ie, a concept where we get hire but none of the bunker and port cost exposure on round trip Houston back to Houston. However, with delivery of Stena Provence for the first voyage starting in Houston we can consider the ballast leg Rdj to Houston on our account which is 19,58 days approx. We have also built in the VMS generation a ballast leg from Brazil back to Houston upon completion of discharge which extends the voyage to 68,2 days (only paid for 48,63 days). The next CVC #2 will be generated as open Houston discharge Brazil and back open Houston which should match the TC hire agreed. \n\nVessel\tStena Provence\nVoy#\t2204\nFix#\tJ GLOB TC/CVC 1\nC/P Date\tJun 29, 2022\nCharterer\tJ Global E\nBroker\tBrazilship\nStart\tRio de Janeiro\nLoad\tTexas City, Houston\nDischarge\tMaceio, Rio de Janeiro\nCargo\t45,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tAug 15-17, 2022 (00:00-00:00)\nRate\t$25,000.00/mt\nComm\tCharterer: 1.25%, Broker: 1.25%, Agent: 1%\nTCE\nPnL\t$10,572.56 for 68.2 days\n($336k) bss 15,5 pd \nDemurrage\t$25,000.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-30T14:32:44.603","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"earnings updated due to days changed and ballast consumption updated"}],"offhireList":[{"id":192575,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":103357,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}